  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this study to investigate, if learning and recall of a sequence of body
      movements (steps that realize a pattern on the ground) can be improved by self-produced music
      (having particular melodic-structures in relation to the pattern), compared to the same sound
      (a single tone) for each pattern in persons with multiple sclerosis compared to age and
      gender matched controls
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
